    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "founder_role",
      "label": "Title",
      "default": "Founder & CEO"
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "founder_body",
      "label": "Bio",
      "default": "<p>Pete Olander built Happie at the intersection of finance, wellness, and plant medicine. His career started on Wall Street — working at J.P. Morgan and First Western Trust Bank — before moving into the consumer wellness space with Nutrition53, where he gained deep experience in CPG product development and brand building.</p><p>At Nutrition53, Pete worked alongside professional athletes and leading experts in the wellness space, developing a deep understanding of what functional ingredients can actually do when formulated with care and intention. That experience shaped his conviction: hemp-derived cannabinoids and functional mushrooms could reshape how people think about social drinking and daily wellness.</p><p>In 2019, he launched Happie — and soon after, relocated operations to California to get closer to the plant, immerse himself in the culture, and understand firsthand what quality means in this industry. From sourcing to formulation, the goal was simple: bring the highest quality ingredients from farm to table for every customer. That commitment to transparency and craft is what drives Happie today, as the brand scales across DTC, Amazon and a growing network of retail and distributor partners nationwide.</p>"
    },
